Subject: BUG: Discrete variables treated as Boolean if used as input/output
To: atacs-bugs <atacs-bugs@vlsigroup.ece.utah.edu>
Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary=485b395e7ae9f2c65f049e282c53

--485b395e7ae9f2c65f049e282c53
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1

The mode (input/output/internal) affects the variable type. In the attached
LPN file, variables x, y and z are internal, input and output separately.
They are all discrete variables and have the same initial values. But the
LPN parser treats y and z as Boolean instead of integer, and only x is
treated as integer.

.inputs y
.outputs z
.internal x
.dummy t2 t1 t0
#@.variables z y x
#|.places p2 p1 p0
.graph
p2 t2
p1 t1
p0 t0
.marking {p2 p1 p0 }
#@.init_vals {<z=5><y=5><x=5>}
#@.enablings {<t2=[z>3]><t1=[y>3]><t0=[x>3]>}
#@.delay_assignments {<t2=[3]><t1=[3]><t0=[3]>}
#@.continuous
.end


-- 
Zhen Zhang

--485b395e7ae9f2c65f049e282c53
